<p><strong>Saving Throws</strong> Con +4, Wis +2</p>

<p><strong>Skills</strong> Perception +4, Stealth +5, Survival +4</p>

<p><strong>Condition Immunities</strong> frightened</p>

<p><strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 60 ft.</p>

<p><strong>Languages</strong> Abyssal, Draconic</p>

<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 4 (1,100 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Hold Breath.</em></strong> The lizardfolk can hold its breath for 15 minutes.</p>

<p><strong><em>Skewer.</em></strong> Once per turn, when the lizardfolk makes a melee attack with its trident and hits, the target takes an extra 10 (3d6) damage, and the lizardfolk gains temporary hit points equal to the extra damage dealt.</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Multiattack.</em></strong> The lizardfolk makes two attacks: one with its bite and one with its claws or trident or two melee attacks with its trident.</p>

<p><strong><em>Bite.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +5 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 6 (1d6 + 3) piercing damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Claws.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +5 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 5 (1d4 + 3) slashing damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Trident.</em></strong> Melee or Ranged Weapon Attack: +5 to hit, reach 5 ft. or range 20/60 ft., one target. Hit: 6 (1d6 + 3) piercing damage, or 7 (1d8 + 3) piercing damage if used with two hands to make a melee attack.</p>

